theorem
|: ( a * M ) :| = ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| )
proof
A1: (( len ( a * M ) ) = ( len M ) & ( width ( a * M ) ) = ( width M )) by MATRIXR1:27;
( len ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) ) = ( len |: M :| ) by MATRIXR1:27;
then A2: ( len ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) ) = ( len M ) by CKB7:def 1;
A3: (for i holds (for j holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices |: ( a * M ) :| ) implies ( |: ( a * M ) :| * (i,j) ) = ( ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) * (i,j) ))))
proof
A4: ( Indices ( a * M ) ) = ( Indices M ) by MATRIXR1:28;
A5: ( Indices ( a * M ) ) = ( Indices M ) by MATRIXR1:28;
let i;
let j;
assume A6: [ i,j ] in ( Indices |: ( a * M ) :| );
A7: ( Indices |: ( a * M ) :| ) = ( Indices ( a * M ) ) by CKB33:1;
then A8: ( |: ( a * M ) :| * (i,j) ) = ( abs ( ( a * M ) * (i,j) ) ) by A6,CKB7:def 1
.= ( abs ( a * ( M * (i,j) ) ) ) by A6,A7,A4,CKB32:1
.= ( ( abs a ) * ( abs ( M * (i,j) ) ) ) by COMPLEX1:65;
( Indices |: M :| ) = ( Indices M ) by CKB33:1;
then ( ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( abs a ) * ( |: M :| * (i,j) ) ) by A6,A7,A5,CKB32:1
.= ( |: ( a * M ) :| * (i,j) ) by A6,A7,A8,A5,CKB7:def 1;
hence thesis;
end;
( width ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) ) = ( width |: M :| ) by MATRIXR1:27;
then A9: ( width ( ( abs a ) * |: M :| ) ) = ( width M ) by CKB7:def 1;
(( len |: ( a * M ) :| ) = ( len ( a * M ) ) & ( width |: ( a * M ) :| ) = ( width ( a * M ) )) by CKB7:def 1;
hence thesis by A1,A2,A9,A3,MATRIX_1:21;
end;
